{# templates/vault/wiki.j2 — vault page for type=synthesis.

   Defines the canonical shape of a synthesis hub page. Inputs
   are the structured fields a synthesis agent populates; the
   template arranges them into the wiki-style layout the vault
   expects.

   Required:
     title           string — hub title (also the # heading).
     rationale       string ≥80 chars — opening paragraph; sits
                            BEFORE the ``## Overview`` heading.
     overview        string ≥200 chars — multi-paragraph prose
                            for the ``## Overview`` body.
     ascii_diagram   string ≥4 lines, ≥80 chars — the hub's
                            illustration; rendered inside a
                            fenced code block.
     key_concepts    list of {name, summary}
                            Rendered as ``- [[Name]] - summary``
                            bullets. ≥3 entries.

   Optional:
     worked_examples list of {title, body} — case studies.
     discussion      list of {topic, summary, actors?}, ≤3
                            entries. Each renders as a
                            ``### topic`` subsection with a
                            framing paragraph followed by an
                            actor list (when actors are
                            identified). actors is a list of
                            {name, argument}; empty / omitted
                            when the source frames the topic
                            but does not name participants.
     sources         list of vault paths — frontmatter entries.

   Inline wikilink discipline (the agent's responsibility, not
   the template's): in every prose field — rationale, overview,
   key_concepts.<i>.summary, worked_examples.<i>.body,
   discussion.<i>.summary — the FIRST occurrence of any atomic
   name MUST be wrapped as a wikilink. ``[[Name]]`` resolves to
   an atomic page when one exists; otherwise the post-gate
   strip-dead-links task rewrites it to plain text.
-#}
---
type: synthesis
title: "{{ title }}"
{%- if sources is defined and sources %}
sources:
{%- for src in sources %}
  - "{{ src }}"
{%- endfor %}
{%- endif %}
last_updated: {{ today }}
---

# {{ title }}

{{ rationale }}

## Overview

{{ overview }}

```
{{ ascii_diagram }}
```

## Key Concepts

{% for c in key_concepts -%}
- [[{{ c.name }}]] - {{ c.summary }}
{% endfor -%}
{%- if worked_examples is defined and worked_examples %}

## Worked Examples

{% for ex in worked_examples -%}
### {{ ex.title }}

{{ ex.body }}

{% endfor -%}
{%- endif -%}
{%- if discussion is defined and discussion %}

## Discussion

{% for d in discussion -%}
### {{ d.topic }}

{{ d.summary }}
{% if d.get('actors') %}
{% for a in d.actors -%}
- [[{{ a.name }}]] - {{ a.argument }}
{% endfor -%}
{% endif %}
{% endfor -%}
{%- endif %}
